ri; Bourdieu; Habermas; Jameson; and Said. Each chapter provides biographical information and details about the thinker's intellectual context, an explanation of key concepts, an outline of the major angles of the theorist's work, an indication of ways in which their theory has been applied and suggestions for further reading. This text is designed as a companion to From Kant to Levi-Strauss: The Background to Contemporary Critical Theory, which is also edited by Jon Simons and published by Edinburgh University Press.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh1 aDobson, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEden, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodchild, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeffernan, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHegarty, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLloyd, Maya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahar, Cheleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcManus, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorris, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharman, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimons, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStafford, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStavrakakis, Yannis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTormey, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo